columns.name: Application ID
columns.description: An identification number assigned by DCA to record each application received.

columns.name: License Number
columns.description: An identification number issued to businesses/individuals to operate legally for the duration of their license term.

columns.name: License Type
columns.description:
DCA offers two license types:
Business. License is issued to an entity/organization based on their address.
Individual. License is issued to an individual person.

columns.name: Application or Renewal
columns.description:
This indicates if it is a new application (i.e., applicant does not currently hold a DCA license) or a renewal (i.e.,
applicant holds a DCA license that is about to expire).

columns.name: Business Name
columns.description:
Applicant’s business name. Note that for individual-license types, the business name is the person’s first name and
last name.

columns.name: Status
columns.description:
This indicates the status of an application. Note that vehicle-operating businesses with pending application status
may operate legally if they have a Temporary Operating Letter. Please refer to Active Vehicles column.

columns.name: Start Date
columns.description:
Date when all application requirements are received. Note that if application status is pending, a start date will not
appear.

columns.name: End Date
columns.description:
Date when DCA has reviewed all application requirements and will issue a license or Temporary Operating Letter
OR deny license application OR when applicant has withdrawn their license application.

columns.name: Temp Op Letter Issued
columns.description:
DCA may issue a Temporary Operating (Op) Letter to certain applicants while their license application is being
reviewed. This allows the business to legally operate for a specific time period.

columns.name: Temp Op Letter Expiration
columns.description: Expiration date of Temporary Operating (Op) Letter.

columns.name: License Category
columns.description: The type of industry that requires a DCA license.

columns.name: Application Category
columns.description:
Applications are categorized as either Basic or Special. Special applications require additional documentation and/or
liaising with external agencies. The following license categories are considered special applications:
 Amusement Arcade
 Amusement Device Permanent
 Amusement Device Portable
 Bingo Game Operator
 Cabaret
 Catering Establishment
 Commercial Lessor
 Employment Agency
 Games of Chance
 Gaming Cafe
 General Vendor
 Home Improvement Contractor
 Home Improvement Salesperson
 Newsstand
 Pedicab Business
 Sidewalk Cafe
 Sightseeing Bus
 Special Sale
 Tow Truck Company
 Tow Truck Exemption

columns.name: Building Number
columns.description: The building number of the business’s address.

columns.name: Street
columns.description: The street name of the business’s address.

columns.name: Street 2
columns.description: The cross-street of the business’s address.

columns.name: Unit Type
columns.description: The unit type of the business’s address (e.g., Apartment/Suite/Other).

columns.name: Unit
columns.description: The unit number of the business’s address.

columns.name: Description
columns.description: Additional description of the location of the business.

columns.name: City
columns.description: The city where the business is located.

columns.name: State
columns.description: The state where the business is located.

columns.name: Zip
columns.description: The zip code where the business is located.

columns.name: Contact Phone
columns.description: Contact telephone number for license applicant.

columns.name: Longitude
columns.description: Longitude of applicant’s business address.

columns.name: Latitude
columns.description: Latitude of applicant’s business address.

columns.name: Active Vehicles
columns.description:
For vehicle-operating businesses with a pending application status, this is the list of vehicles certified to operate
along with corresponding medallion numbers.

view.description: This data set features license applications received during the last and current calendar years, including applications where a license was issued, denied, withdrawn, or remains pending. For a list of legally operating businesses, please refer to the DCA – Legally Operating Businesses data set. This data set is updated on a weekly basis.
